EMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM

This is a non-responding Facility.   The Facility has coordinated emergency response activities with its local emergency response agency and local fire department.

FIVE YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY

There have been no on-site deaths, injuries, or significant property damage; or off-site deaths, injuries, property damage, evacuations, or sheltering in place, in the past five (5) years because of the ammonia operations at this Facility.

PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY

The Facility will address each recommendation listed in the December 2024 process hazard analysis (PHA). In summary, the PHA recommendations include, but are not limited to:

	Implement the Helena RMPr program;
	Replace hydrostatic relief valves that are expired and/or are rated greater than the process MAWP;
	Replace the damaged pressure relief valve on the compressor;
	Replace expired liquid and vapor transfer hoses;
	Adjust installation of the breakaway devices to be in accordance with the Manufacturer's installation instructions;
	Install a pressure gauge on the discharge side of the liquid pump;
	Perform and document a leak test on the underground piping;
	Obtain and maintain historical Operating Procedures Annual Certifications and Mechanical Integrity records;
	Replace faded NFPA labels on the PVs;
	Coordinate emergency notification with response agencies; and
	Update the Facility RMP program to reflect the EPA RMP rule changes published on May 2024.    

